At least one suspected case of Coronavirus also refferred to as ‘COVID-19’ has been reported in Adamawa State. According to reports, the suspected case, a  returnee from Kano, who earlier submitted himself for test. Even though the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC). Is yet to confirm the development publicly, the  man,  has been on self-isolation since returning to the state from Kano last week. Also, the state government is yet to officially announce the case. When contacted, Chairman of the committee, who is also Secretary to the State Government, Bashiru Ahmad, simply said, “I will call you back.”